INSERT INTO tbl_program_courses VALUES("13","Project Management Professional","","In the world of today, project management skills have become the backbone and yardstick to measure the competency of professionals. In the industry, Project Management Professional (PMP) is the most recognised certification for project managers. Unlike other professional certifications which are career or geography specific, PMP cuts across all areas of human endeavour and equally has a world-wide coverage in its study. As a PMP, one has the capacity to work in virtually any industry and location irrespective of the methodology adopted by the industry.","","<p> As a project manager, you will have the opportunity of managing projects from inception to the time of delivery. PMP increases your earning potential as certified project managers earn relatively more than their non-certified counterparts.</p> <p> The demand for certified project managers by employers is on the increase as industries stand a better chance of competing favourably in the market if more than one-third of their employees are certified in project management.</p> <p> The PMP training not only helps a person in learning fundamentals of project management in terms of scope, time, risk, communication, resource allocation but also help them in becoming better managers and marketing agents. The PMP signifies that you speak and understand the global language of project management and connects you to a community of professionals, organizations and experts worldwide. Become&nbsp;</p>","","Structure","Project Management Professional (PMP) There are five project management process groups which includes; 1. Initiating. 2. Planning. 3. Executing. 4. Monitoring and Controlling. 5. Closing.","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","Active");
INSERT INTO tbl_program_courses VALUES("14","MSc in Digital Marketing","","It covers many bases and goes by various names online marketing, digital marketing, e-marketing, internet marketing  but whatever you call it, this is without question one of the most important sectors for anyone involved in marketing today. And a Masters in Digital Marketing degree will prepare you for many exciting roles in this fast-changing and fast-growing sector.","","<p> First of all, what is digital marketing? Digital marketing is the promotion of brands or products via one or more forms of digital media. The rise of smart phones, apps, and other forms of &lsquo;new media&rsquo; in the past decade has meant that digital marketers need to be able to connect with consumers through various devices and digital platforms, including social media. Digital marketing combines the creativity of developing new and interesting ways to get the marketing campaign&rsquo;s message across, with the technical side of keeping track of data, digital engineering and analytics.</p> <h2> <strong>What will I learn</strong></h2> <p> The careful balance of theory and practice within the course is designed to help active professionals make further strides within their career and within the Digital Marketing industry.&nbsp;</p> <p> Analytical insight into the role of digital marketing in business and its current contribution to boosting effectiveness and efficiency within companies.</p> <p> &nbsp;</p> <p> The vital operational skills needed to successfully implement online advertising campaigns, social media marketing, e-CRM and web data analysis.</p> <p> &nbsp;</p> <p> The necessary balance of conceptual understanding and hands-on skills to make professionals of the course highly sought after by potential recruiters.</p>","","","","","","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","","","","<p> Coming Soon!!</p>","","Active");
